PS IT Infrastructure & Services Limited Key Developments

PS IT Infrastructure & Services Limited Reports Audited Earnings Results for Fourth Quarter and Full Year Ended March 31, 2017
May 30 17
PS IT Infrastructure & Services Limited reported audited earnings results for fourth quarter and full year ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported income from operations of INR 1,153.05 million, loss from operations before other income and finance costs and exceptional items of INR 2.264 million, loss from ordinary activities before tax of INR 3.497 million, net loss of INR 3.628 million or 0.007 per basic and diluted share compared to the income from operations of INR 1,061.203 million, loss from operations before other income and finance costs and exceptional items of INR 2.015 million, loss from ordinary activities before tax of INR 6.307 million, net loss of INR 8.266 million or 0.015 per basic and diluted share for the same quarter a year ago. 

For the year, the company reported income from operations of INR 3,180.274 million, loss from operations before other income and finance costs and exceptional items of INR 0.914 million, profit from ordinary activities before tax of INR 0.424 million, net profit of INR 0.293 million or 0.001 per basic and diluted share compared to the income from operations of INR 3,283.602 million, profit from operations before other income and finance costs and exceptional items of INR 1.262 million, profit from ordinary activities before tax of INR 3.971 million, net profit of INR 2.012 million or 0.004 per basic and diluted share for the previous year.


PS IT Infrastructure & Services Limited, Board Meeting, May 30, 2017
May 26 17
PS IT Infrastructure & Services Limited, Board Meeting, May 30, 2017. Agenda: To consider the audited results.


PS IT Infrastructure & Services Limited, Board Meeting, Feb 28, 2017
Feb 20 17
PS IT Infrastructure & Services Limited, Board Meeting, Feb 28, 2017. Agenda: To evaluate the performance of Board of Directors and Key Managerial Personnel of the company; to review the performance of the Chairperson of the company; and to assess the Quality, quantity and timelines of flow of information between the Company management and the Board.


